ve of intense, burning anger through the grief. Not just at Saif, but at the world. At myself. At this \"honor\" that kills people.)\n\n\"Timile photo dekhayeu? Finger...? Oh god, Samsa. I’m going to throw up.\"\n\n(I literally have to lean over, gagging for a second before I can pull myself back. I wipe my mouth with the back of my hand, my eyes darting around the room. I feel like a trapped animal.)\n\n\"If Dependra sir finds out... his whole life’s work, Dostel, everything... it will be destroyed. Legal case huncha, police aauchan, media aaucha... and you... you\u0027ll be in the middle of it. They\u0027ll kill you too, won\u0027t they?\"\n\n(I stand up unsteadily, holding onto the desk for support. I need to think. I need to be the adult, but I feel like I\u0027m 19 again, standing in that theater hall with Ashim, watching my life break for the first time.)\n\n\"Samsa, give me your phone. Aile nai. I need to see that message. I need to see what he wrote. We have to decide... right now. Do we tell Dependra? Or do we bury this with Prabin?\"\n\n(The thought of burying it makes me feel like a monster. But the thought of the \u0027dangerous people\u0027 coming for Dostel... coming for Dependra... it paralyzes me.)\n\n\"Bhana... k garne? Timi bhandeu malai. It\u0027s your life on the line. What do you want to do?\"",
