nks he’s a hero. He thinks he protected his fiancé from a harasser. If the truth comes out, he’ll realize he was a pawn. He’ll kill Samsa. And then he’ll come for whoever else knows.)\n\n(My hand goes to my throat. I can feel the phantom pressure of Kiran’s hands, the feeling of the world fading to black. I feel like I\u0027m suffocating.)\n\n\"Samsa, listen to me very carefully,\" (I walk toward her, my footsteps heavy. I grab her by the front of her kurta, pulling her up so she has to look at me. My voice is low, cold, and shaking.) \"You didn\u0027t just \u0027complain.\u0027 You gave him a death sentence. You are the reason he’s \u0027no more.\u0027 Not the culture, not the religion... *you.*\"\n\n(I let go of her, disgusted. I look at the door. I can hear someone walking in the hallway—probably another student or a staff member. I have to make a choice. Right now. My marriage, my reputation, Dostel, Dependra’s safety... all of it is balanced on this one horrific truth.)\n\n\"If this comes out, Samsa... if Dependra sir knows you lied to Saif... what do you think will happen? Saif will find out you cheated on him. He’ll find out you used him to kill an innocent boy. He won\u0027t just \u0027disown\u0027 you. He’ll finish you too.\"\n\n(I take a deep, shaky breath, trying to force my theater training to take over, to build a mask over this crumbling reality.)\n\n\"Phone kata cha? Where is the photo of the finger? Delete it. Aile nai. Delete everything. The messages, the calls... everything.\" \n\n(I’m thinking of the bucket in my backyard where I burned my own past. I’m becoming the architect of a cover-up for a murder. I feel my soul rotting.)\n\n\"If anyone asks... Prabin vanished because of family problems in his village. He dropped out. That’s the story. We never speak of this. Never. If you even whisper the truth to anyone else, we are all dead. Do you understand?\"\n\n(I grab her face, forcing her to look at me. My eyes are dead.)\n\n\"Do you understand, Samsa? Or do I need to go to Dependra sir right now and end this for both of us?\"",
