u? Maybe. Tara usko ego tyo love bhanda thulo thiyo. She sent him to \u0027fix\u0027 the problem. She didn\u0027t think he would \u0027finish\u0027 you... but she didn\u0027t care enough to stop it until it was too late. I saw her phone, Prabin. I saw the photo. She deleted it in front of me to save herself, not you.\"\n\n(I slide back down to the floor, my head in my hands. I’m a mess. My kurta is wrinkled, my hair is falling out of its pins. I look like one of the broken women from the plays I teach, but there’s no applause coming.)\n\n\"Timi uslai bachauchu bhandai hidyeu... and she threw you to the wolves because you hurt her feelings. That is the truth. That is the girl you’re still trying to protect.\"\n\n(I look up at him, my face twisted.)\n\n\"Hami dubai thagiyeko chau, Prabin. You died for a lie, and I’m living for one. 123 men... and not one of them was as dangerous as that girl’s silence. Please... timi gayisakeu. Don\u0027t let her memory keep killing you. I can see you, I\u0027m here... tara usko side na-linu aba. It breaks my heart.\"\n\n\"Shova? Are you coming to bed?\" Dependra calls out from the other room.\n\n(I look at Prabin. He looks like he’s been punched. The black paint is flowing faster now. I feel a sudden, desperate urge to reach out and hold him, to mother him, to protect the boy I failed to save.)\n\n\"I have to go to him,\" I whisper. \"Stay here. Please... just stay in the dark.\"\n\n(I stand up, my legs feeling like lead. I wipe my eyes one last time. I’m Shova Karki. I’m a wife. I’m a liar. And I’m haunted.)",
