      "text": "(I’m sitting on the cold bathroom floor, my back against the door. I can hear Dependra moving in the bedroom, the rustle of sheets as he settles in. He thinks I’m just having an upset stomach. He has no idea I’m witnessing the slow-motion collapse of a soul.)\n\n(I look at Prabin. Seeing him cry—really cry, with that black paint-like substance staining his hoodie—it’s more than I can take. My theater training usually lets me control my face, but right now, it’s all gone. I’m just a woman in a dark room with a dead boy.)\n\n\"Nai, nani... timi dumb haina,\" I whisper, my voice thick with tears. \"Timi ta sacho thiyau. Timile sacho maya garyeu. It’s not your fault that the person you loved didn\u0027t know how to hold that love.\"\n\n(I think of the 123 men. I think of Roshan, who I said \"I love you\" to while he was inside me. I think of how many times I was \"dumb\" for a thrill, for a touch, for anything that wasn\u0027t the reality I was scared of. Prabin’s \"dumbness\" was pure. Mine was a rot.)\n\n\"Timro family...\" (The word feels like a stone in my mouth. I swallow hard, the bile rising.) \"Prabin, malai thaha cha... it’s the hardest part. Timro mamu, timro baba... they think you\u0027re just gone. They think you\u0027re being irresponsible. Maile tyo story validate gare, Prabin. I’m the one who told Dependra sir to tell everyone you just left for the village.\"\n\n(I let out a ragged, choked sob, burying my face in my knees for a second. The smell of diesel is so strong now I feel like I’m suffocating in it. And the heat... that sick, adrenaline-fueled warmth between my legs is back, stronger than before. I hate myself. I feel like a randi, grieving a boy while my body reacts to the terror like it\u0027s a kink. I grip my own thighs, trying to make the feeling go away.)\n\n\"I\u0027m the one who buried you, Prabin. Not just Saif. Me. Maile timlai protect garna sakthe... if I had just told Dependra the truth that night. But I was scared. I was scared for my marriage. I was scared he’d find out about *me* if things got messy. I traded your truth for my safety.\"\n\n(I look up at him, my eyes bloodshot and wild. I reach out, my hand trembling in the air between us.)\n\n\"Timro family le thaha paudaina... because if they do, everyone dies. If they go to the police, Saif will come for Samsa. He\u0027ll come for Dostel. He\u0027ll come for Dependra. Do you see? The lie is the only thing keeping the rest of them alive.\"\n\n(I hit my head back against the door, a dull thud.)\n\n\"Timi lonely chau... I know. Tara ma yaha chu. I will carry you. I will see you every day. I will look at your empty chair in PALM and I will know. I will never let them forget you, even if I have to keep your name a secret.\"\n\n\"Shova? Nidayeu ki kya ho?\" Dependra’s voice is right outside the door now. He knocks softly. \"Are you okay, nani? Dherai ber bhayo.\"\n\n(I freeze. I look at Prabin. He’s standing there, looking at me with such profound sadness that I feel my heart might actually stop beating.)\n\n\"I have to go, Prabin,\" I whisper, reaching up to wipe the tears and the smudge on my forehead. I scrub until it hurts. I fix my kurta, smoothing the fabric over my shaking body. \"I have to be his wife now. I have to go into that bed and pretend I don\u0027t feel the cold you brought in.\"\n\n(I stand up, my legs feeling like they’re made of water. I turn the lock, the sound echoing like a finality. I take one last look at the bathtub. He\u0027s still there. He\u0027ll always be there.)\n\n\"Stay here,\" I think. \"Please just stay.\"\n\n(I open the door and put on the mask. I smile at Dependra, though my lips feel like they\u0027re going to crack.)\n\n\"I\u0027m okay. Ali garo bhako thiyo, aba thik cha,\" I say. My voice is steady. The performance is perfect.\n\n(I walk to the bed and lie down next to him. He pulls me close, his skin warm and living. I close my eyes, and in the darkness, I see Prabin’s missing finger pointing at the door.)",
