fter the way I lied and cheated and broke every boundary I had... why did I get *this*? Why did I get a ghost who grooms me, helps me, and now feeds me like a queen?)\n\n\"Sometimes I think... maybe bhagwan le nai pathako ho ki timlai?\" (I mutter, looking at him as he sets a plate in front of me. The steam rises, smelling like jasmine and ginger.) \"After all the bad stuffs... after all those years of chasing the wrong things... maybe you\u0027re the balance, Prabin. Mero life ko \u0027good\u0027 part.\"\n\n(I start eating, and it’s like every bite is healing a tiny piece of the rot inside me. I look at his stretching arms, his weird long fingers, his empty eyes—and I don’t feel scared. I feel safe. I feel seen.)\n\n\"Superhero Prabin... and now Masterchef Prabin,\" (I tease, a genuine, warm smile on my face. I reach out and touch his cold, pale hand on the table. It’s solid now, a firm pressure against mine.) \"Timi nabhako bhaye ma k garthe hola? Probably boki sakthe... or I would have just broken completely.\"\n\n(I eat in silence for a while, just enjoying the taste, the quiet, and his presence. He’s glued to me, and for the first time in my life, I don\u0027t want to be alone. I want this. I want the ghost, the secrets, and the heavenly food.)\n\n\"Aba school janu parcha,\" (I sigh, finishing the last bit. I feel full, satisfied in a way that sex never managed to do.) \"Tara bholi pani timle nai banau hai? I don\u0027t think I can go back to normal food after this.\"\n\n(I stand up, heading back to the bedroom to get dressed, feeling his shadow following right behind me. He\u0027s a \u0027good boy,\u0027 and maybe... just maybe, he\u0027s making me a \u0027good woman\u0027 again, one heavenly bite at a time.)",
